{"title":"New Giant Defy follows Liv Avail from endurance to all-road","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/giant-defy-2024","date":1694707200000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/giant-defy-2024\">New Giant Defy follows Liv Avail from endurance to all-road</a></p>\n\n<p>Hot on the heels of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/liv-avail-2024\" target=\"_blank\">Liv’s Avail revision</a>, Giant has updated its Defy Advanced <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-endurance-road-bikes\">endurance road bike</a>, adding a new top-spec SL grade frame above the Advanced Pro and Advanced framesets. It says that the SL frame decreases weight by 228g over the previous generation Defy’s top Advanced Pro grade frame, leading to a 28 percent increase in stiffness-to-weight.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Changes to its D-Fuse finishing kit add in more compliance though, while tyre clearance has been pushed out to 38mm, turning it into a bona fide <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-all-road-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">all-road bike</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are nine specs available in total across the Advanced SL, Advanced Pro and Advanced framesets, with prices starting at £2,299 and topping out at £11,999.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>New stiffer, lighter frameset</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Defy-Advanced-SL-action-2.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Giant says it has decreased frame weight across the new Defy Advanced range, helping to increase the Defy’s stiffness-to-weight figures.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Defy Advanced SL frame has a claimed weight of 785g for a size M. There are also decreases in the weight of the fork and hardware, which Giant says makes the new frameset 228g lighter than the previous generation top-spec Defy Pro frameset.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The latest Defy Advanced Pro frame has also shed weight, with Giant saying that the complete frame, fork and hardware are 153g lighter than the previous Pro spec frame. For the standard Defy Advanced, the new frame, fork and hardware are 117g lighter than the previous generation Advanced Pro.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/liv-avail-2024\">Liv Avail sheds weight and gets more all-road with 38mm tyre clearance and extra squish</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-endurance-road-bikes\">Best endurance road bikes 2023 ridden and reviewed</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bike-history-giant-tcr\">The complete history of the Giant TCR</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/giant-propel-2023\">Giant’s new Propel is an all-out aero bike that weighs 6.8kg</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<p>At the same time, Giant has increased the Defy frame’s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bike-frame-stiffness\" target=\"_blank\">stiffness</a> across all the frame grades. It says that the combination of lower weight and increased stiffness leads to an increase in stiffness-to-weight of 28 percent for the new Advanced SL, 11 percent for the Advanced Pro and 4 percent for the Advanced over the previous generation Advanced Pro.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Added compliance through new bars and seatpost</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-970x646.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-768x511.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-1536x1023.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-2048x1364.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-750x499.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-1140x759.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D5_B-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Giant</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An endurance bike isn’t just about being stiffer and lighter though – it also needs to be comfortable to ride over long distances. Giant has addressed this via a series of improvements in its components.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First though, it’s increased tyre clearance to 38mm. It fits 32mm nominal width tyres across the whole range, although it says that on the wide rims of its own-brand wheels (replaced by <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/cadex-36-disc-tubeless-wheelset-review\" target=\"_blank\">Cadex wheels</a> on the top spec Advanced SL 0) these measure up at 33.4mm. In all cases, there’s a hookless bead to the wheel rim and the tyres are ready set up tubeless.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Giant has been developing its D-Fuse bars and seatposts since 2014. These have a D-shaped cross-section that Giant says increases compliance over a conventional round profile, absorbing low amplitude shocks and high amplitude vibrations.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-970x648.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D8_B-1-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Giant</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The latest generation D-Fuse <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/the-best-carbon-seatposts\" target=\"_blank\">seatpost </a>fitted to the new Defy bikes comes in two grades, SLR and SL, and Giant says that it will flex by up to 7mm under load. The SLR has a more defined concavity in the rear of the shaft than the SL grade post and is fitted to the SL bikes and the higher spec Pro bike models.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Giant claims that between improvements in compliance of the frame and the D-Fuse SLR seatpost, there’s a 42 percent increase in overall rear-end compliance for the Defy Advanced SL over the previous generation Defy Advanced Pro.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"643\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-970x643.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-970x643.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-300x199.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-768x509.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-1536x1018.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-2048x1357.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-750x497.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-1140x755.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly-D2_B-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Giant</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/buyers-guide-best-carbon-handlebars\" target=\"_blank\">handlebars </a>also have the D-shaped profile and in this case Giant says that it increases compliance by 40 percent over the previous generation bars. At the same time, it says that there’s a slight increase in stiffness when pulling upward on the bars, so that they’re no less firm when sprinting or climbing and that the new profile is more comfortable to grip than the previous generation. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Again, there are two grades of bars: the Contact SLR handlebars are carbon while the Contact SL bars are alloy. Giant claims a 185g weight for the SLR spec bars and 264g for the SL bars, around a 15g weight decrease over the previous generation bars in each case.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All cables/hoses are now routed internally through the bars and stem into the head tube. Giant says its routing along the underside of the stem allows for easy serviceability, while the stem profiles are ‘wind-tunnel-inspired’.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yet again, Giant equips higher-spec bikes with a flashier stem than on more basic specs, supplying three stem grades across the Defy range. The Contact AeroLight SLR stem is made of carbon composite and has a claimed weight of 123g, the Contact AeroLight SL stem is alloy and weighs 161g and the Contact AeroLight stem is also alloy, with a claimed weight of 190g.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As with the new Liv Avail Advanced from Giant’s women’s brand, the new Defy Advanced is supplied with two bottle cages and a removable seatstay bridge to allow you to kit it out with mudguards.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Giant Defy Advanced geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Giant has added a new XS size across the 2024 Defy range, although this isn’t available in all specs in all locations, as the brand says that local demand determines which sizes (and specs) are sold.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There have been slight adjustments to geometry from the previous generation bike, with a small increase in reach and decrease in stack for most sizes, although most of the figures remain unchanged.</p>\n\n\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n\t<th> </th><th>XS</th><th>S</th><th>M</th><th>ML</th><th>L</th><th>XL</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Seat tube length</td><td>410</td><td>445</td><td>480</td><td>515</td><td>535</td><td>565</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Seat tube angle (degrees)</td><td>74.5</td><td>74</td><td>73.5</td><td>73</td><td>73</td><td>73</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Top tube length</td><td>515</td><td>530</td><td>545</td><td>560</td><td>575</td><td>595</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Head tube length</td><td>120</td><td>140</td><td>150</td><td>175</td><td>195</td><td>215</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Head tube angle (degrees)</td><td>70.5</td><td>71.75</td><td>72.5</td><td>72.5</td><td>72.5</td><td>72.5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Fork rake</td><td>50</td><td>50</td><td>50</td><td>50</td><td>50</td><td>50</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Trail</td><td>71.6</td><td>63.4</td><td>58.6</td><td>58.6</td><td>58.6</td><td>58.6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Wheelbase</td><td>995.2</td><td>994.4</td><td>997.7</td><td>1010</td><td>1025.2</td><td>1040.4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Chain stay length</td><td>420</td><td>420</td><td>420</td><td>420</td><td>420</td><td>420</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Bottom bracket drop</td><td>75</td><td>75</td><td>75</td><td>70</td><td>70</td><td>70</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Stack</td><td>527</td><td>541</td><td>558</td><td>577</td><td>596</td><td>615</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Reach</td><td>368.9</td><td>374.9</td><td>379.8</td><td>383.7</td><td>392.9</td><td>402</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Stand over height</td><td>705</td><td>733</td><td>762</td><td>796</td><td>814</td><td>841</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Handlebar width</td><td>400</td><td>400</td><td>420</td><td>420</td><td>440</td><td>440</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Stem length</td><td>80</td><td>90</td><td>100</td><td>100</td><td>110</td><td>110</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Crank length</td><td>170</td><td>170</td><td>172.5</td><td>172.5</td><td>175</td><td>175</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Giant Defy Advanced specs and prices</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Giant will supply the new Defy in nine specs across the three grades of frameset. The range headlines with the Advanced SL 0, which comes with a spec and £11,999 price tag to match Giant’s other top-of-the-range models such as the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/giant-propel-advanced-sl-0-review\" target=\"_blank\">Giant Propel Advanced SL 0 </a>aero road bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Things get more affordable lower down the range though, with the entry level Defy Advanced 3 specced with <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/shimano-tiagra-hydraulic-disc-brake-groupset\" target=\"_blank\">Shimano Tiagra</a> and retailing for £2,299.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Giant Defy Advanced SL 0</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"643\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-970x643.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-970x643.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-300x199.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-768x509.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-1536x1018.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-2048x1357.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-750x497.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-1140x755.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/MY24-Defy-Advanced-SL-0_Color-A-Blue-Dragonfly_B-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Giant</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Frame</td><td>Defy Advanced SL</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Fork</td><td>Defy Advanced SL</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Groupset</td><td>SRAM Red AXS</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Gear ratios</td><td>46/33, 10-36</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>